ITALY DAYBOOK: Draghi Speaks at Conference on Italian Economy

-- B y   T o m m a s o   E b h a r d t
-- 
2011-10-12T05:02:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-12/italy-daybook-central-bank-s-draghi-speaks-at-conference-on-italy-economy.html
Bank of Italy  Governor  Mario Draghi 
speaks at conference on  Italy  and the World Economy 1861-2011,
in  Rome . Italy’s President Giorgio Napolitano is also scheduled
to attend the conference.  Defense Minister Ignazio La Russa said the government may
hold a confidence vote after Italy’s Parliament failed to
approve the government’s 2010 budget, Ansa reported citing the
minister.  EQUITIES:
*Intesa Sanpaolo SpA (ISP IM) and two other Italian banks had
their credit ratings cut by  Fitch Ratings  and UniCredit SpA (UCG
IM) was placed on review. Fitch downgraded Intesa’s long-term
issuer default ratings, viability ratings to A/a from AA-/aa-.
Union di Banche Italiane SCPA’s (UBI IM) ratings were reduced to
A-/a- from A/a and Banca Monte dei Paschi di Siena SpA (BMPS
IM)was cut to BBB+/bbb+ from A-/a-.  ECONOMY:
* European Central Bank Executive Board member Lorenzo Bini
Smaghi speaks in a panel discussion about the future of the
euro. 6 p.m. in Milan.  MARKETS:
*The benchmark  FTSE MIB Index (FTSEMIB)  fell 0.39 percent to 16,036.14.
*The  yield spread  on 10-year Italian bonds and similar German
securities widened 4.78 basis points to 353.60 basis points.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tommaso Ebhardt in Milan at 
 tebhardt@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chad Thomas at   cthomas16@bloomberg.net . 